SUMMARY:Ethics - Week 1: Beyond Yourself? Principles of Moral Architecture
DESCRIPTION:EWMBA 207 - Ethics & Responsible Business Leadership\nProf. Jonathan Weigel\n\nWeek 1 (Blue): Monday March 30\, 2026\n6:00-9:30 PM PT\n\nTopic: Beyond yourself? Principles of moral architecture\n\nObjectives:\n- Managerial application: Moral architecture for organizations\n- Explore structural forces (organizational\, legal\, market-related) and psychological tendencies behind fraudulent behavior\n- Conversations on what values to uphold\n\nPreparation Guidelines:\n- Are there limits to self-interest as a principle on which to run organizations/society?\n- Can you highlight structural and psychological factors behind the Theranos downfall?\n- Would values that depart from self-interest help avoid Theranos-like cases? What alternative values?\n- What are your non-negotiables?\n\nRequired Readings:\n- Dal Bo and Xu / How did a $9 Billion Health Tech Startup End up DOA?\n- Griffith / The Ugly Unethical Underside of Silicon Valley\n- Zimbardo / The Psychology of Power: To the Person? To the Situation? To the System?\n- The Inventor: Out For Blood In Silicon Valley (2019) - HBO Documentary\n\nAssignments Due Before Class:\n- Assignment 1a: Opinion survey (optional)\n- Assignment 1b: My experience (graded - contributes to participation)\n\nGrading: Participation 30% | Quizzes 10% | Midterm 25% | Final 35%\n\nCourse Page: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1550881
LOCATION:N370 Chou Hall
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1550881
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
