SUMMARY:Ethics - Week 3: MIDTERM EXAM + Theories of Justice
DESCRIPTION:EWMBA 207 - Ethics & Responsible Business Leadership\nProf. Jonathan Weigel\n\nWeek 3 (Blue): Monday April 13\, 2026\n6:00-9:30 PM PT\n\n*** MIDTERM EXAM - First Half of Class ***\nOpen-notes\, individual exam via bCourses. Bring your laptop.\nAvailable for download at 6:00 PM. Submit within allotted time.\n\nSecond Half: Theories of Justice\n\nObjectives:\n- Mid-term examination (graded quiz\, in-person)\n- Normative Frameworks (Justice): Economic inequality and distribution\n- Two contrasting 20th-century theories of justice\n\nPreparation Guidelines:\n- Is justice primarily about processes or about outcomes?\n- Are there forms of discrimination that are acceptable\, while others are not?\n- How much is your success determined by luck vs. effort?\n- Who is the relevant "worst off" party when applying the maximin criterion?\n\nReadings for Second Half:\n- Sandel: Excerpts from Justice\, Chapter 6 - The Case for Equality\n- Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy: Justice as Entitlements\n\nOptional Midterm Prep:\n- Assignment 2: Google's Dragonfly\n- Assignment 3: Inclusive Organizations\n\nCourse Page: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1550881
LOCATION:N370 Chou Hall
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1550881
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
